Wi-Fi (IEEE 802.11):​
Transfers data between the tablet and the Laptop Data Processing Center via HTTP/REST (JSON) requests.​

DMX512:​
Controls professional DMX lighting systems from the Arduino Microcontroller.​

BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy):​
Transmits real-time physiological data from the Apple Watch to the tablet.​

USB Serial Communication:​
Sends control commands from the Laptop to the Arduino Microcontroller.​

HDMI:​
Delivers high-definition visual content from the Laptop Data Processing Center to the projector.​

​GPIO/PWM Signals：
Controls LED ambient lighting and audio systems via the Arduino.
